author: Written by: FOX8Live.com Staff
title: Gunman robs St. Charles Ave. Subway during business hours
text:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) - A St. Charles Ave. Subway restaurant was robbed at gunpoint Wednesday night during business hours.
The incident happened around 9:10 p.m. Wednesday in the 2000 block of St. Charles Ave.
Officers said that a gunman entered the store and demanded cash from the register. The cashier complied and the suspect fled the scene.
The robbery comes in the wake of increased security at several Uptown businesses. Three prominent businesses – Patois, Atchafalaya and Monkey Hill Bar – were robbed during business hours in August and September. No arrests have been made in any of the cases.
Anyone with information on the incident is asked to contact Crimestoppers at (504) 822-1111.
